      <description>&lt;!-- Summary of Article (70 Words)  &#xA;&#xA;# Table Of Contents  &#xA;&#xA;&lt;nav id=&#34;TableOfContents&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;ul&gt;&#xA;    &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#source-policy-definition-id&#34;&gt;Source Policy Definition ID&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;    &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#duplicating-the-policy-to-be-modified&#34;&gt;Duplicating The Policy To Be Modified&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;    &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#modifying-the-properties&#34;&gt;Modifying The Properties&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;    &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#modifying-the-policy-rule&#34;&gt;Modifying The Policy Rule&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;    &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#modifying-the-parameters&#34;&gt;Modifying The Parameters&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;    &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#putting-it-all-together&#34;&gt;Putting It All Together&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;    &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#creating-the-custom-policy-definition&#34;&gt;Creating The Custom Policy Definition&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;/nav&gt;  &#xA; --&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;There may well come a time when there isn&amp;rsquo;t a Built In Azure Policy that meets your needs, and you need to either modify an existing policy, or create new a policy from scratch.  Creating custom policies should always be a last resort, as the BuiltIn policies Azure provides are kept up to date and version controlled by Microsoft.  As soon as you create a custom policy, you are responsible for maintaining it when capability is added or deprecated.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
